President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Ohio and ordered federal assistance to aid in the recovery efforts from the COVID-19 pandemic. Federal funding will be provided to state and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency protective measures. James K. Joseph has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on assessments and requests from the state. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.